Rego Arch Mage<br>
Healers of Norrath</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kohrian>Kohrian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/02 1:24:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7868.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Buy a Horse!</span><hr size=1> Basically while on a horse you are medding as long as you are not fighting or moving.  This means you can med and cast at the same time, which is a tremendous manaregen advantage.  You also avoid sit-down aggro, especially from nearby wandering adds or on incoming.<br>
<br>
With a few charisma items you should be able to get a horse for about 7.5kpp (or maybe a little less) in the bazaar.  Granted, its slower than spit, but its a great investment. <p>Zarros Livinglight<br>
55th Templar of Tunare<br>
Wings of the Chimera<br>
Saryrn<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanukdandiprat>ShanukDandiprat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/02 2:16:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7868.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Buy a Horse!</span><hr size=1> <br>
Horse is definately good to have for a mage.  <br>
<br>
On a horse, I can happily nuke away while medding the whole time, and never have to worry about getting eaten the second I sit down.  With some spells, you can even med back to full before you finish casting the spell, which is cool the first time you see it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also, your movement rate on a horse is not affected by encumbrance, which can be handy.  You also get an innate safe fall of like 150 on a horse (but who cares when you can summon lev rings?).<br>
<br>
There are a couple of disadvantages though.<br>
<br>
First one is that you can't interrupt your spell by ducking, which can be irritating.<br>
<br>
Second is that you can't make fine, quick movements while on a horse.  This is due to very slow acceleration/decceleration and excruciatingly slow strafe.  This make positioning a water pet a real pain.<br>
<br>
Overall, horse is great.<br>
<br>
Shanuk Dandiprat<br>
Conjurer of Drinal<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balasarius>Balasarius</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Italics</span><br>  Posts: 368<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/02 2:22:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7868.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Buy a Horse!</span><hr size=1> Horses suck.<br>
