<br>
On a horse you have aggro like you are standing.<br>
<br>
On a horse part of your view is obstructed by the horses head.<br>
<br>
On a horse it is a little difficult, but not impossible to loot, unless on a slope or close to a wall, which can make it nearly impossible.<br>
<br>
On a horse you have added safefall.<br>
<br>
On the cheapest horse it takes a little time to get up to speed and slow down. An expencive horse is better at this.<br>
<br>
The cheapest horse is only a little faster than standard run speed and significantly slower than run 3.<br>
<br>
On a horse it is close to impossible to hand or recieve items to others, on a horse or not.<br>
<br>
A horse is hungry, and it is easy to accidently eat food like stat food.<br>
<br>
If you have a horse and run 3, be prepared to ditch the horse at first sign of trubble.<br>
<br>
Disabeling horse models removes some of the disadvantages named above.<br>
<br>
